Comment [#9 to bug 269820][1] explains how to delete the search index, which appears to be the solution to a corrupt index whose symptoms are the dreaded

&gt; An internal error occurred during: &quot;Items filtering&quot;.&lt;br /&gt;
&gt; Class file name must end with .class

message box.

How to delete the search index:

 1. Close Eclipse
 2. Delete &lt;tt&gt;&amp;lt;workspace&amp;gt;/.metadata/.plugins/org.eclipse.jdt.core/*.index&lt;/tt&gt;
 3. Delete &lt;tt&gt;&amp;lt;workspace&amp;gt;/.metadata/.plugins/org.eclipse.jdt.core/savedIndexNames.txt&lt;/tt&gt;
 4. Start Eclipse again

  [1]: https://bugs.eclipse.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=269820#c9
